methodology_notes.joint_modeling: XGBoost joint models predict SCR and EM simultaneously, then calculate Quote = EM/SCR
methodology_notes.normalization: All targets normalized to [-1,1] scale using MinMaxScaler fitted on training data only
methodology_notes.evaluation: Performance compared using normalized RMSE for fair comparison across targets

key_findings: Joint XGBoost modeling achieved 27.2% improvement over direct Quote prediction
ZSK1 (interest rate factor) is the most important feature across all models
XGBoost models showed superior performance for multi-output regression tasks
Polynomial features (degree 2) were most effective for individual target prediction
